[@slide] Three ways it could play out
[@subtitle] Even the conservative case clears the bar
[@note] Anchor on the base case. Conservative still returns 42% — the downside is acceptable, the upside is large. [/@note]

[compare]
  | Scenario | Adoption | ROI | Payback | Proceed |
  | Conservative | 35% | 42% | 3.8 yrs | y |
  | *Base case | 52% | 91% | 2.6 yrs | y |
  | Aggressive | 68% | 148% | 1.9 yrs | y |
[/compare]

[@slide dark] Risks, with eyes open
[@subtitle] Probability · Impact
[@note] We are not hiding the risks. The mitigation is the phased rollout — we prove adoption in pilots before committing the full spend. [/@note]

[status]
  [item state:risk title:"Regulatory change" owner:"Med · High"] new cross-border rules across markets [/item]
  [item state:warn title:"Integration delays" owner:"Med · Med"] complex logistics workflows [/item]
  [item state:warn title:"Competitive response" owner:"High · Med"] incumbents defend their share [/item]
  [item state:risk title:"Slower adoption" owner:"Med · High"] SMEs are slow to switch tools [/item]
[/status]

[callout tone:warn icon:scale] A phased pilot caps exposure — we scale only on proven uptake. [/callout]

